     abstract = "{Weak gravitational lensing observations probe the spectrum and evolution
        of density fluctuations and the cosmological parameters that
        govern them. The nonlinear evolution of large-scale structure
        produces a non-Gaussian signal that is potentially observable in
        galaxy shear data. We study the three-point statistics of the
        convergence, specifically the bispectrum, using the dark matter
        halo approach, which describes the density field in terms of
        correlations between and within dark matter halos. Our approach
        allows us to study the effect of the mass distribution in
