        rare massive halos (clusters) in observed fields. We show that
        the convergence skewness is primarily due to rare and massive
        dark matter halos, with skewness converging to its mean value
        only if halos of mass M>{}10$^{15}$ M$_{solar}$ are present.
        This calculational method can in principle be used to correct
        for such a bias as well as to search for more robust statistics
        related to the two- and three-point correlations.}",
